From fac7bea482166d69eb8c37e8642370c667ac72dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:22:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] Implement zxdg_decoration_manager_v1 and use native
 decorations

Owl places every toplevel into a real Cocoa window, so create those
windows with the native title bar and resize controls by default,
and advertise the xdg-decoration protocol, always answering that
decorations are server side. This stops clients like foot from
drawing their own decorations on top of the native ones. For
clients that draw decorations regardless, the SSD can still be
toggled off from the window menu.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
